    explanation: '"Keystone predator" most precisely names what a sea otter is in the example: a predator whose removal causes cascading effects throughout the ecosystem. B is correct. A ("decomposer") describes organisms that break down dead material. C ("primary producer") describes photosynthetic organisms — kelp itself is a primary producer. D ("symbiont") describes a mutually beneficial relationship, not predation.',
