    passage: 'Cognitive scientists have found that expertise in a domain changes not just the quantity but the quality of what practitioners perceive. A novice chess player looking at a mid-game board sees individual pieces in isolated positions; a grandmaster perceives meaningful patterns — clusters of pieces whose relationships encode strategic threats and opportunities. This shift from seeing elements to seeing _______ is a hallmark of expertise across many domains, from radiology to architecture to music.',
