    answer: 'B', isSPR: false,
    explanation: 'The passage provides two reasons why sentinels benefit personally: they are recently fed (lower cost), and signaling their presence reduces their own predation risk. The behavior benefits the group (warning of predators) but also benefits the individual sentinel. B correctly captures this dual benefit. A ("randomly distributed") contradicts the finding that recently fed meerkats serve as sentinels. C ("driven entirely by kin selection") introduces a specific mechanism the passage does not support — the signaling-to-predators benefit is not kin-selection-based. D ("deceptive signaling") contradicts the "honest signaling" characterization in the passage.',
